AGI - A committee of interests > in Palermo, formed by public administrators, Masons and mafias, for the construction of a shopping mall. Three arrests of the Carabinieri of the Provincial Command of Palermo, at the request of the Dda (one in prison and two to the domiciles), for external competition in association mafiosa>, extortion aggravated by the mafia method, corruption, traffic of illicit influences aggravated by having favored the mafia association.
&nbsp;
The military arrested Mimmo Russo>, former municipal councilman of FdI and recognized face to Palermo, in particular in the world of precarious workers: is accused of external competition in mafia association and political-mafia exchange vote. For this reason the measure was placed by the gip of Palermo Walter Turtirici who welcomed the requests of the prosecutor Maurizio de Lucia, the adjunct Marzia Sabella and the deputy Andrea Fusco. The gip has placed precautionary custody for Russo and house arrests for Gregorio Marchese and Achilles Andò.
&nbsp;
The measure arises from the investigations of the investigative nucleus of the carabinieri of Palermo >, in the period 2020/2023, on delegation of the Dda of Palermo in order to the relationship existing between a unionist, local administrator of the metropolitan commune, in office until June 2022, and exponents of Cosa nostra palermitana. The existence of a committee of interests emerged, of which a dealer belonging to the Freemasonry was also a member, engaged in the construction of a mall in the Sicilian capital. In this context, the political exponent has worked in favour of the approval of a variant to the Town Regulatory Plan, aimed at modifying from agricultural to commercial area the destination of land on which the structure should have arisen; it would have obtained - as a counterpart - a large number of recruitments in building the mall, to promise people related to organized crime, in exchange for the electoral support of the mafia organization.
&nbsp;
The investigation also unveiled the heavy ingestion that the politician exercised towards the company that manages the racecourse of Palermo >, conditioning its work so that it bends to the will of its mafia referents and concuring with them in the committee of aggravated extortions, to the detriment of free professionals who had carried out assignments on behalf of that economic-sports reality and who were forced, with all threat, to give up The investigation, finally, has reconstructed the promise obtained by the politician of a package of assumptions in a society that deals with the great food distribution, in exchange for facilitations at the offices of the commune of Palermo and a post of sub-government to be attributed to a representative of the same commercial society.

