AGI - More than eight Italians out of 10 (83%) demand the stop to imports of agri-food products that do not respect the same rules as Italian ones in the matter of food security, environmental and protection of the work. This is what emerges from an investigation Coldiretti/Ixè widespread to Brennero, with ten thousand farmers, led by the national president Ettore Prandini, who in the two days will come to the borders to defend the health of the citizens and the income of the companies from the invasion of foreign food that often ends on the tables spread as Italian.
For the occasion the table of the "fake in Italy", Italian sounding of our house, with a real menu from the first to the dessert made with lasagna to the Bolognese, arrosticini Abruzzo, lenticchie umbre all of foreign origin. With the start of the collection of signatures for a European law of popular initiative on the obligation to label the origin of all products on the market.
<div </div
&nbsp;
Coldiretti aims to expose the phenomenon of imported and camoufled foods as Italians thanks to minimal processing, reviewing the criterion of the last substantial transformation. But the collection of signatures, which can be supported by signing in all the peasant markets of Campagna Amica and in the offices Coldiretti and "will be promoted also on social media with the hashtag #nofakeinitaly, also aims to finally put in transparency - continues Coldiretti - all those products that are still anonymous and that represent about a fifth of the expenditure of Italians and include food symbol starting from bread. In fact, it is not necessary to indicate the origin of the wheat used, as happens for pasta. And the same goes for all derivatives like biscuits, crackers and the like."
"From all anonymity also the legumes in box, perhaps sold in a package with colors or signs that recall the Italian ' - notes Coldiretti - as well as the fruit or vegetable jams transformed, like jams and subli. No label of origin also for vegetables and fruits of IV Gamma and nuts and shellfish, for which should open a spire from next year, neither for rabbit and horse meat. The courses on the menus of restaurants are also completely anonymous."
"We have to say enough to unfair competition, stop counterfeit foods passing through borders and European ports - said the president of Coldiretti Ettore Prandini - Our mobilization, in continuity with the work done in Brussels in these months, continues to defend the income of farmers and to safeguard the health of citizens". &nbsp;
